The Department of Petroleum Resources (DPR) has issued Licence To Establish (LTE) the first floating LNG production plant for the processing of 176MMcfd natural gas and condensate to UTM Offshore Limited, an indigenous oil and gas company at a presentation ceremony at the DPR headquarters Abuja on Monday. According to statement endorsed and sent the Head, Public Affairs DPR, Paul osu saying The Director/CEO, DPR Sarki Auwalu while presenting the licence explained that the milestone was a reinforcement of the promise andÂ commitment of President Muhammadu Buhari to Nigerians to promote indigenous participation in the oil and gas sector and ensure that companies come to Nigeria and do business in an equitable way to stimulate the economy and create jobs for Nigerians.   Auwalu further stated that the licence was a demonstration of governments resolve to harness safe and reliable technology for the development of the oil and gas industry.   CEO assured stakeholders that DPR will continue to create opportunities and enable business for companies by providing the regulatory tools of licences, permits and approvals for investors.   The Managing Director of UTM Offshore Ltd, Mr. Julius Rone while receiving the licence promised to abide with the terms of issuance within the twenty four months validity period of the LTE from the date of issue.